        <mxCell id="q0CeVz2YIgJOeLPyzCkL-1" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Figure 2 – C4 Container Diagram&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br/&gt;This diagram presents the internal container level architecture of the Campus Device Loan System. It shows the major application containers and how they communicate within the system. Key containers include the web application interface, the API service responsible for business logic, background worker services, Azure Service Bus for event driven communication, and the Azure SQL database for persistent storage. The diagram also illustrates integration with external services such as authentication, monitoring and the university inventory system. This view demonstrates how the application is structured using a cloud native and distributed architecture.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
